## High-Quality Testing Framework with Cypress, Docker, and Screenshots

This example outlines a basic structure for a high-quality Cypress testing framework, incorporating best practices for using Docker and capturing screenshots.

**Project Structure:**

```
cypress-project/
├── cypress/
│   └── fixtures/
│       └── 
├── cypress/support/
│   ├── commands.js
│   ├── login.js
│   └── fixtures.js
├── cypress/tests/
│   ├── integration/
│   │   └──
│   ├── cypress/tests/integration/
│   │   ├── **login.js**
│   │   ├── **screenshots.js**
│   │   └── **components/**
│       ├── login.js
│       └── **other-components.js**
├── cypress/tests/e2e/
│   ├── **smoke-tests.js**
│   ├── **regression-tests.js**
│   └── **positive-tests.js**
├── cypress/support/
│   └── **negative-tests.js**
├── cypress/support/
│   └── **e2e-tests.js**
├── cypress/tests/
│   └── **login-tests.js**
├── cypress.json
└── cypress/

```

**1. `cypress/index.js`:**

This file will contain the custom commands for your test suite.

```javascript
// cypress/index.js

// Example of a custom command
Cypress.Commands.add('loginToApp', (username, password) => {
  cy.visit('/login');
  cy.get('#username').type(username);
  cy.get('#password').type(password);
  cy.get('button[type="submit"]').click();
});

// Add a custom command to capture a screenshot
Cypress.Commands.add('takeScreenshot', (name = 'screenshot') => {
  cy.screenshot(name);
});

// Define the `takeScreenshot` command
// This command takes a screenshot and saves it with a timestamped filename
Cypress.Commands.add('takeScreenshot', (name = 'screenshot') => {
  cy.get('body').screenshot(`cypress/screenshots/${Cypress.mocha.suite.title}/${name}.png`);
});

// Example of using the custom command
cy.loginToApp('user@example.com', 'password123');

// Example of using the custom command in a test
describe('Login Functionality', () => {
  it('Should successfully log in', () => {
    cy.visit('https://example.com'); // Navigate to the login page
    cy.fixture('user').then(user => {
      cy.get('#username').then(input => {
        cy.takeScreenshot('login-page'); // Take a screenshot
      });
      // ... rest of your test code ...
  });
```

